PAC_MAN Dragon Edition

Authors: Amar Parkash Singh
	 Rohan D'Souza

## Running the game

### Option 1: Build a standalone executable (recommended)

This project includes scripts to package the game as a native app using `jpackage`.

**Windows prerequisites**
1. Install JDK 21+ (must include `jpackage`)
2. Download JavaFX SDK 21 from https://gluonhq.com/products/javafx/
3. Download JavaFX jmods 21 (same version as your JDK)

Set environment variables (Command Prompt):

```cmd
set JAVA_HOME=C:\Program Files\Eclipse Adoptium\jdk-21.0.8
set JAVAFX_HOME=C:\javafx-sdk-21.0.8
set JAVAFX_JMODS=C:\javafx-jmods-21.0.8
```

Build and run:

```cmd
git clone https://github.com/rdso323/Pacman-Game.git
cd Pacman-Game
scripts\build.bat
scripts\launch.bat
```

The installed game lives at:

```text
%LOCALAPPDATA%\PacManDragon\baseline\PacManDragon-baseline\
```

Build an improved version for comparison:

```cmd
scripts\build.bat improved
scripts\launch.bat improved
```

If the `.exe` shows "Failed to launch JVM", run `scripts\diagnose.bat` to see the real error in a console window.

See `BUILD.md` for Linux instructions, troubleshooting, and full details.

### Option 2: Run from Eclipse (development)

1. Clone the repository
2. Open Eclipse
3. File -> Open Projects From File System -> select the repo folder
4. Open `PACMAN -> Launcher.java` or `PACMAN -> Main.java`
5. Run as Java Application (requires JavaFX SDK on the module path)

## Notes

The background music sometimes stops playing. This is due to Java garbage collection behavior in the original project. Packaged builds catch audio startup failures so the game still launches.

